```plantuml
@startuml marekq_rss-lambda
participant CloudWatch as "CloudWatch\n(Event Schedule)"
participant StepFunction as "Step Function\n(rssblog)"
participant LambdaCrawl as "Lambda\n(rsscrawl)"
participant LambdaGetFeed as "Lambda\n(rssgetfeed)"
participant DynamoDB as "DynamoDB"
participant Comprehend as "AWS Comprehend"
participant SES as "AWS SES"
participant S3 as "S3"
participant Algolia as "Algolia\n(Optional)"
participant AppSync as "AppSync\n(Optional)"

CloudWatch -> StepFunction : Triggers (scheduled)
StepFunction -> LambdaCrawl : Invoke
LambdaCrawl -> S3 : Check existing data
S3 --> LambdaCrawl : Return existing data
LambdaCrawl -> StepFunction : Return feed list
StepFunction -> LambdaGetFeed : Invoke (parallel for each feed)
LambdaGetFeed -> DynamoDB : Check for existing posts
DynamoDB --> LambdaGetFeed : Return post status
LambdaGetFeed -> Comprehend : Extract entities (tags)
Comprehend --> LambdaGetFeed : Return entities
LambdaGetFeed -> DynamoDB : Store post data
LambdaGetFeed -> SES : Send notification (if enabled)
LambdaGetFeed -> Algolia : Index post (if enabled)
LambdaGetFeed -> S3 : Store public JSON (if enabled)
LambdaGetFeed --> StepFunction : Return processing result
StepFunction --> CloudWatch : Completion status

AppSync -> DynamoDB : Query posts (if enabled)
DynamoDB --> AppSync : Return post data
@enduml
```